  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I arrived to the partisans, and I have to be interviewed through the commandant, Szczerbiec, of the partisans, Szczerbiec.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in a little house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was invited inside with my friend, Riszik Riszfeld.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they start to ask us, did you for any-- the only one reason that brought you here is to save your heads, that is the reason why you come to the partisans?",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He knows that we are Jews, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only one that knows that we are Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was the person that also he spoke questions.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I said to him, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we came here, I think, to fight our enemy, the Germans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Hmm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The second question, do you know-- [CHUCKLES] do you know when we were taking Vilna, that was in 1920, liberating Vilna for Poland, he was an army-- officer in the army, General [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was the army that was liberated Vilna, next to Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That I said to him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And he-- he mentioned another thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He said, when we were-- the question was that when we were liberating Vilna from the city, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were shooting to us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I said, no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Think that the-- the [NON-ENGLISH] Street, 90% of Jews or more, might be 95% of Jews, were leaving there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My answer was I finished gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I-- I read a lot, and I know that what we were told, that [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when Vilna was liberated and next to Poland, that the population were greeting the liberators with [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] bread and salt.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
